===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|suffixum||suffix}}, from {{m|la|sub||under, beneath}} + {{m|la|fixus}}, perfect passive participle of {{m|la|figere||to fasten, fix}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{qualifier|noun}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-suffix.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{qualifier|verb}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/|/səˈfɪks/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪks|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# One or more letters or sounds [[added]] at the [[end]] of a word to modify the word's [[meaning]].
#: ''The '''suffix''' "-able" changes "sing" into "singable".''
# {{lb|en|mathematics}} A [[subscript]].

====Usage notes====
* The plural {{m|en|suffices}} occasionally appears (including in one educational publication), but it is not a standard plural.

